<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schwarzhans &amp; Ohe &amp; Tsuchiya &amp; Ujihara" authorityYear="2022" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Lampanyctus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lampanyctus lenticularis" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenticularis">Lampanyctus lenticularis</taxonomicName>
(Latin) = lens-shaped, referring to the regular outline and small size of the otoliths.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="holoytpe">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Holoytpe.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
