<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. A-J: Lampanyctus lenticularis sp. nov., Tsuyama City, Takakura Formation; B-D: holotype, SMF PO 101.121, level h; A, E-J: paratypes, SMF PO 101.122, levels f, g, h, j; K-M: Lampanyctus profestus Schwarzhans, 2019, SMF PO 101.123, Tsuyama City, Takakura Formation, level MS 36; N-V: Lampanyctus tsuyamaensis sp. nov., Tsuyama City, Takakura Formation; N-P: holotype, SMF PO 101.124, level MS 15; Q-V: paratypes, SMF PO 101.125, levels MS 15, MS 36, MS 90; W-AJ: Stenobrachius ohashii sp. nov.; W-Y: holotype, SMF PO 101.126, Yatsuo machi, Toyama City, Kurosedani Formation, level K 5; Z-AB, AF-AJ: paratypes, SMF PO 101.127, Tsuyama City, Takakura Formation, levels MS 15, MS 70; AC-AD: paratype, SMF PO 101.128, Niimi City, Bihoku Group; AE: paratype, SMF PO 101.129, Fuchu machi, Toyama City, Higashibessho Formation, level H 21; AK-AM: Stenobrachius leucopsarus (Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann, 1890), Recent, coll. Schwarzhans, leg. Fitch, off California; AN-AO: Stenobrachius nannochir (Gilbert, 1890), Recent, NSMT-P. 63309, 36 ° 28 ' N, 141 ° 10 ' E." figureDoi="10.3897/zitteliana.96.83571.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694120" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">7B-D</figureCitation>
